[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     46[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Description:** The function iterates through segments once and merges short segments into neighbors. However, merging a short segment can create a new boundary that produces another short segment (if two short segments are adjacent). A single pass won't catch cascading merges. For the synthetic data in this example it works fine, but a learner applying this to real noisy predictions might get unexpected results. This is a known limitation of single-pass approaches.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     47[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Suggested fix:** Add a comment: `# NOTE: Single pass. For very noisy predictions, you might need to iterate until stable.`
